{ZERO}: At the end of your opponent's turn, if your opponent put a creature into the battle zone for no cost, you may put this D2 Field from your hand into the battle zone for no cost.
(Whenever another D2 Field is put into the battle zone, put this D2 Field into your graveyard.)
D2 WRAP Denjara Switch—At the start of your turn, you may turn this D2 Field upside down for the rest of the game. If you do, destroy one of your opponent's tapped creatures.}

■ (This creature is put into your mana zone tapped.)
{DOUBLE BREAKER}
■ Whenever this creature attacks, you may discard a Dragon from your hand. If you do, this turn, this creature gets "triple breaker", and you may put the top 2 cards of your deck into your mana zone.

■ (This creature is put into your mana zone tapped.)
{SYMPATHY}: Earth Eater and Giant (This creature costs 1 less to summon for each of your Earth Eater, Giant in play. It can't cost less than 2.)}
■ When you put this creature into the battle zone, you may draw a card for each of your Earth Eaters in the battle zone. Then you may draw a card for each of your Giants in the battle zone.
